# mbuzz Pricing

Machine-readable pricing for AI agents and procurement automation. Human version: https://mbuzz.co/pricing.

| Plan | Monthly price (USD) | Events / month | Custom DSL models | Ad platform integrations | Overage |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Free | $0 | 30,000 | 0 | 0 | None — events drop after cap |
| Starter | $29 | 1,000,000 | 3 | 2 | $5 per 250,000 events |
| Growth | $99 | 5,000,000 | 5 | 5 | $15 per 1,000,000 events |
| Pro | $299 | 25,000,000 | 10 | Unlimited | $50 per 5,000,000 events |

## What every plan includes

- All 8 attribution models: first-touch, last-touch, linear, time-decay, position-based, Markov chain, Shapley value, data-driven
- Attribution DSL editor (Free includes 0 custom model slots; paid plans add 3, 5, or 10)
- Server-side tracking — captures 30–40% more touchpoints than client-side
- Open-source SDKs: Ruby, Node, Python, PHP, Shopify, server-side GTM
- Real-time event debugging
- Attribution + funnel + spend dashboards
- LTV/CLV mode (toggle between transaction count and customer lifetime value)
- Full data ownership — CSV export, API access, MCP server for agent-native pulls
- No vendor lock-in, no premium-tier export gate

## What paid plans add

- Google Ads spend sync (live today)
- Meta Ads spend sync (coming)
- LinkedIn Ads spend sync (coming)
- Custom DSL model slots (3 / 5 / 10)
- More ad platform integrations (2 / 5 / unlimited)

## Definitions

- **Event**: one tracked touchpoint in a customer journey — pageview, click, signup, purchase, or any custom event sent to the mbuzz API.
- **Custom DSL model**: an attribution model written or forked using the Attribution DSL (a SQL-like language with nested time windows, custom decay curves, segment-specific logic).
- **Ad platform integration**: a connected ad platform account whose spend mbuzz pulls and reconciles against tracked conversions.

## Terms

- Month-to-month billing. No annual contract. Cancel any time.
- Overage is charged at the end of the billing period at the rates above. No surprise invoices, no hard cutoffs on paid plans.
- Free tier hard-caps at 30,000 events. No overage — events beyond the cap are dropped until the next billing cycle or you upgrade.

## Enterprise

For more than 25,000,000 events/month, custom integrations, or a commercial agreement: https://mbuzz.co/contact.

## Comparison anchor

For context: enterprise MTA (Dreamdata, HockeyStack pre-pivot, Rockerbox) starts at $1,400–$5,000/month. Incrementality / MMM platforms (Haus, Measured, Recast, Mutinex) range from $10,000–$132,000/year. mbuzz's $0–$299/month tier covers the $1M–$100M revenue companies that fall between those two markets.

